article.headline: UC Davis 66, UC Irvine 63
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Thomas Juillerat sank four free throws in the final minutes to help UC Davis to a 66-63 victory over UC Irvine on Wednesday. Juillerat made a pair of free throws with 2:15 remaining to give the Aggies their first lead, 60-59, since the opening minute. He hit two more with 55 seconds to play to make it 64-61. Irvine (4-8) got a career-best 17 points from Adam Metelski, but could not avoid a fifth consecutive loss. The Anteaters have not won since defeating San Jose State on Dec. 3. Metelski connected on 5-of-6 shots for 11 points in the first half as Irvine led 34-28 at the break. Phil Rasmussen and Vince Oliver led UC Davis with 15 points each as the Aggies (4-9) ended a two-game losing skid. Rommel Marentez added 14 points.
